    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `ollama rename` Feature\n\n**4 files modified · No new files · No test files touched**\n\n### Changes at a glance\n\n| File | What's added |\n|------|-------------|\n| `api/types.go` | `RenameRequest` struct (after `CopyRequest`, ~line 764) |\n| `api/client.go` | `Rename()` client method (after `Copy`, ~line 387) |\n| `server/routes.go` | `RenameHandler` method + route registration |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | `RenameHandler` CLI func + `renameCmd` cobra command |\n\n---\n\n### API types — `api/types.go`\nAdds `RenameRequest` with the same two fields as `CopyRequest`:\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Client method — `api/client.go`\nMirrors `Copy` exactly, posting to `/api/rename`:\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error { ... }\n```\n\n### Server handler — `server/routes.go`\n`RenameHandler` (inserted after `CopyHandler`) does:\n1. Bind + validate JSON body → 400 on error\n2. Parse & resolve source via `getExistingName` → 400 if name is invalid\n3. **`manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)`** → **404** if source not found\n4. Parse & resolve destination → 400 if name is invalid\n5. **`manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` succeeds** → **409 Conflict** if destination exists\n6. `CopyModel(src, dst)` — copies manifest only; blobs are shared\n7. `srcManifest.Remove()` — deletes source manifest + prunes empty dirs\n8. `srcManifest.RemoveLayers()` — **safe no-op here**: destination manifest now references all blobs, so nothing is orphaned\n9. Returns HTTP 200 with no body\n\nRoute registered with: `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` (after the copy route, ~line 1698).\n\n### CLI command — `cmd/cmd.go`\n```\nollama rename SOURCE DESTINATION\n```\n- `cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n- Prints `renamed 'SOURCE' to 'DESTINATION'` on success\n\nAll supporting functions (`getExistingName`, `CopyModel`, `ParseNamedManifest`, `Remove`, `RemoveLayers`) already exist — zero new utility code is needed.",
